title: Field hockey rankings for Oct. 8, 2015
text:
Olivia Sahaydak (6) has 7 goals and 14 assists for Liberty, which makes its debut in the rankings this week (lehighvalleylive.com file photo) By Tom Hinkel | For lehighvalleylive.com on October 08, 2015 7:30 AM View/Post Comments 
The top five spots remain unchanged. Emmaus pulled out a 3-2 overtime win over Owen J. Roberts on Saturday on Meredith Sholder's hat trick. Voorhees blanked three opponents last week to maintain the third spot. No. 5 Whitehall posted a hard-fought 2-1 win over Parkland . Easton falls a spot after its loss to Liberty . Speaking of the Hurricanes, they take over the 10th spot this week by virtue of their win over the Red Rovers. Bangor was in line to take that spot until it lost to Pen Argyl , 1-0, on Wednesday. Nazareth , which has lost four straight to fall to 7-8, dropped from the rankings. 
Team (last week's ranking), record 
1. Emmaus (1), 13-0 
2. Moravian Academy (2), 14-0 
3. Voorhees (3), 10-2 
4. Warren Hills (4), 9-1 
5. Whitehall (5), 12-1 
6. Southern Lehigh (7), 14-1 
7. Easton (6), 11-4
